The paper deals with the problem of moving object segmentation in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of Procrustes analysis and energy minimization, which are techniques commonly used in shape analysis (cs.MM) and optimization (cs.LG). The method also involves clustering of trajectories, which is a common technique in graph theory (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.GR, and cs.RO.
